main.name: Lathril, Blade of the Elves
main.oracle_text:
Menace
Whenever Lathril, Blade of the Elves deals combat damage to a player, create that many 1/1 green Elf Warrior creature tokens.
{T}, Tap ten untapped Elves you control: Each opponent loses 10 life and you gain 10 life.

card.name: Canopy Tactician
card.oracle_text:
Other Elves you control get +1/+1.
{T}: Add {G}{G}{G}.
card.flavor_text: "Death and life are two ends of the same spear."

card.name: Elven Ambush
card.oracle_text: Create a 1/1 green Elf Warrior creature token for each Elf you control.
card.flavor_text:
"No elf can match a Tuskeri in combat. Why not charge?"
—Knorjolvin, Tuskeri raider

card.name: Elderfang Ritualist
card.oracle_text: When Elderfang Ritualist dies, return another target Elf card from your graveyard to your hand.
card.flavor_text: Her fingers stiffened as the shrouded corpse stirred. Her final, ragged breath was one of triumph. "Return, my chosen, and grant our people victory!"

card.name: Binding the Old Gods
card.oracle_text:
(As this Saga enters and after your draw step, add a lore counter. Sacrifice after III.)
I — Destroy target nonland permanent an opponent controls.
II — Search your library for a Forest card, put it onto the battlefield tapped, then shuffle.
III — Creatures you control gain deathtouch until end of turn.

card.name: Skemfar Shadowsage
card.oracle_text:
When Skemfar Shadowsage enters, choose one —
• Each opponent loses X life, where X is the greatest number of creatures you control that have a creature type in common.
• You gain X life, where X is the greatest number of creatures you control that have a creature type in common.

card.name: Tergrid's Shadow
card.oracle_text:
Each player sacrifices two creatures.
Foretell {2}{B}{B} (During your turn, you may pay {2} and exile this card from your hand face down. Cast it on a later turn for its foretell cost.)
card.flavor_text: Tergrid, god of fright, never acknowledges her own shadow . . . or its murderous deeds.

card.name: Harald, King of Skemfar
card.oracle_text:
Menace (This creature can't be blocked except by two or more creatures.)
When Harald, King of Skemfar enters, look at the top five cards of your library. You may reveal an Elf, Warrior, or Tyvar card from among them and put it into your hand. Put the rest on the bottom of your library in a random order.

card.name: Roots of Wisdom
card.oracle_text: Mill three cards, then return a land card or Elf card from your graveyard to your hand. If you can't, draw a card. (To mill a card, put the top card of your library into your graveyard.)
card.flavor_text: Though imprisoned in Jaspera trees, the elvish gods known as the Einir still whisper through the ages.

card.name: Jaspera Sentinel
card.oracle_text:
Reach
{T}, Tap an untapped creature you control: Add one mana of any color.
card.flavor_text: The arrows of the elvish elite strike as true and deadly as the fangs of the Cosmos Serpent they revere.

card.name: Skemfar Elderhall
card.oracle_text:
Skemfar Elderhall enters tapped.
{T}: Add {G}.
{2}{B}{B}{G}, {T}, Sacrifice Skemfar Elderhall: Up to one target creature you don't control gets -2/-2 until end of turn. Create two 1/1 green Elf Warrior creature tokens. Activate only as a sorcery.

card.name: Poison the Cup
card.oracle_text:
Destroy target creature. If this spell was foretold, scry 2.
Foretell {1}{B} (During your turn, you may pay {2} and exile this card from your hand face down. Cast it on a later turn for its foretell cost.)
card.flavor_text: Dark schemes cut down what armies cannot.

card.name: Return Upon the Tide
card.oracle_text:
Return target creature card from your graveyard to the battlefield. If it's an Elf, create two 1/1 green Elf Warrior creature tokens.
Foretell {3}{B} (During your turn, you may pay {2} and exile this card from your hand face down. Cast it on a later turn for its foretell cost.)

card.name: Wolverine Riders
card.oracle_text:
At the beginning of each upkeep, create a 1/1 green Elf Warrior creature token.
Whenever another Elf you control enters, you gain life equal to its toughness.
card.flavor_text: "We'll break their lines. The rest of you, follow!"

card.name: Pact of the Serpent
card.oracle_text: Choose a creature type. Target player draws X cards and loses X life, where X is the number of creatures they control of the chosen type.
card.flavor_text: "Our quarrels behind us. Our foes before us. Death or triumph for us all!"

card.name: Ruthless Winnower
card.oracle_text: At the beginning of each player's upkeep, that player sacrifices a non-Elf creature.
card.flavor_text: "I count the usurpers with my dagger, one death blow at a time."

card.name: Elderfang Venom
card.oracle_text:
Attacking Elves you control have deathtouch.
Whenever an Elf you control dies, each opponent loses 1 life and you gain 1 life.
card.flavor_text: "The Cosmos Serpent favored us with his venom. As thanks, we sink fangs into those who dishonor the old ways."

card.name: Serpent's Soul-Jar
card.oracle_text:
Whenever an Elf you control dies, exile it.
{T}, Pay 2 life: Until end of turn, you may cast a creature spell from among cards exiled with Serpent's Soul-Jar.
card.flavor_text: The coils spiral like time itself, carrying spirits back around from death to reawakening.

card.name: Bounty of Skemfar
card.oracle_text: Reveal the top six cards of your library. You may put a land card from among them onto the battlefield tapped and an Elf card from among them into your hand. Put the rest on the bottom of your library in a random order.
card.flavor_text: Even war cannot dull Skemfar's beauty.

card.name: Crown of Skemfar
card.oracle_text:
Enchant creature
Enchanted creature gets +1/+1 for each Elf you control and has reach.
{2}{G}: Return Crown of Skemfar from your graveyard to your hand.
card.flavor_text: Lathril, queen of the ancient Einir, left a powerful legacy for her mortal descendants.

card.name: Eyeblight Cullers
card.oracle_text: When Eyeblight Cullers dies, create three 1/1 green Elf Warrior creature tokens, then mill three cards. (Put the top three cards of your library into your graveyard.)
card.flavor_text:
"As long as eyeblights exist, the hunt will never end."
—Miara, Thorn of the Glade

card.name: Prowess of the Fair
card.oracle_text: Whenever another nontoken Elf is put into your graveyard from the battlefield, you may create a 1/1 green Elf Warrior creature token.
card.flavor_text: An elvish duel is a thing of beauty: the warriors' grace, the crash of steel, then the artful spray of blood.

card.name: Elvish Promenade
card.oracle_text: Create a 1/1 green Elf Warrior creature token for each Elf you control.
card.flavor_text: The faultless and immaculate castes form the lower tiers of elvish society, with the exquisite caste above them. At the pinnacle is the perfect, a consummate blend of aristocrat and predator.

card.name: Imperious Perfect
card.oracle_text:
Other Elves you control get +1/+1.
{G}, {T}: Create a 1/1 green Elf Warrior creature token.
card.flavor_text: In a culture of beauty, the most beautiful are worshipped as gods.

card.name: Lys Alana Huntmaster
card.oracle_text: Whenever you cast an Elf spell, you may create a 1/1 green Elf Warrior creature token.
card.flavor_text: From the highest tiers of Dawn's Light Palace to the deepest shade of Wren's Run, the silver notes of the horn shimmer through the air, and all who hear it feel its pull.

card.name: Abomination of Llanowar
card.oracle_text:
Vigilance; menace (This creature can't be blocked except by two or more creatures.)
Abomination of Llanowar's power and toughness are each equal to the number of Elves you control plus the number of Elf cards in your graveyard.
card.flavor_text: "Run!" screamed its living mouths. "Come!" cried its dead ones.

card.name: Ambition's Cost
card.oracle_text: You draw three cards and you lose 3 life.
card.flavor_text:
"Conquering your first world is the hardest, after all. My power grew as I moved from world to world, taking anything that would make the next taking easier."
—Ob Nixilis

card.name: Arcane Signet
card.oracle_text: {T}: Add one mana of any color in your commander's color identity.
card.flavor_text: It started as a mere drop of water. The Magic Mirror crystallized it into much more.

card.name: Casualties of War
card.oracle_text:
Choose one or more —
• Destroy target artifact.
• Destroy target creature.
• Destroy target enchantment.
• Destroy target land.
• Destroy target planeswalker.

card.name: Beast Whisperer
card.oracle_text: Whenever you cast a creature spell, draw a card.
card.flavor_text: "The tiniest mouse speaks louder to me than all the festival crowds on Tin Street."

card.name: Command Tower
card.oracle_text: {T}: Add one mana of any color in your commander's color identity.
card.flavor_text:
"Approach my tower on bended knee or depart from it as ash upon the wind."
—Gadwick, the Wizened

card.name: Dwynen, Gilt-Leaf Daen
card.oracle_text:
Reach
Other Elf creatures you control get +1/+1.
Whenever Dwynen, Gilt-Leaf Daen attacks, you gain 1 life for each attacking Elf you control.
card.flavor_text: "This is our land. We will not allow eyeblights to poison its beauty."

card.name: Cultivator of Blades
card.oracle_text:
Fabricate 2 (When this creature enters, put two +1/+1 counters on it or create two 1/1 colorless Servo artifact creature tokens.)
Whenever Cultivator of Blades attacks, you may have other attacking creatures get +X/+X until end of turn, where X is Cultivator of Blades's power.

card.name: Elvish Archdruid
card.oracle_text:
Other Elf creatures you control get +1/+1.
{T}: Add {G} for each Elf you control.
card.flavor_text: "The elves tend the forest, and the forest sustains the elves. My role is to ensure that the cycle continues."

card.name: Elvish Mystic
card.oracle_text: {T}: Add {G}.
card.flavor_text:
"Life grows everywhere. My kin merely find those places where it grows strongest."
—Nissa Revane

card.name: Elvish Rejuvenator
card.oracle_text: When Elvish Rejuvenator enters, look at the top five cards of your library. You may put a land card from among them onto the battlefield tapped. Put the rest on the bottom of your library in a random order.

card.name: Farhaven Elf
card.oracle_text: When Farhaven Elf enters, you may search your library for a basic land card, put it onto the battlefield tapped, then shuffle.
card.flavor_text: "Verdant bloom does exist. It merely hides for its own safety."

card.name: End-Raze Forerunners
card.oracle_text:
Vigilance, trample, haste
When End-Raze Forerunners enters, other creatures you control get +2/+2 and gain vigilance and trample until end of turn.
card.flavor_text:
"Smash this city to pieces."
—Domri Rade

card.name: Eyeblight Massacre
card.oracle_text: Non-Elf creatures get -2/-2 until end of turn.
card.flavor_text:
"I've already seen so much evil, so much darkness. Why do you insist on adding more?"
—Nissa Revane, to Dwynen

card.name: Foul Orchard
card.oracle_text:
Foul Orchard enters tapped.
{T}: Add {B} or {G}.
card.flavor_text: The stench of rotting meat lures flies, goblins, and young raptors.

card.name: Golgari Guildgate
card.oracle_text:
Golgari Guildgate enters tapped.
{T}: Add {B} or {G}.
card.flavor_text: Every part of the gate was reclaimed from forgotten ruins and imbued with new purpose by the Swarm.

card.name: Golgari Findbroker
card.oracle_text: When Golgari Findbroker enters, return target permanent card from your graveyard to your hand.
card.flavor_text: "We gather the past from surface dwellers and sell it right back to them."

card.name: Golgari Rot Farm
card.oracle_text:
Golgari Rot Farm enters tapped.
When Golgari Rot Farm enters, return a land you control to its owner's hand.
{T}: Add {B}{G}.

card.name: Jagged-Scar Archers
card.oracle_text:
Jagged-Scar Archers's power and toughness are each equal to the number of Elves you control.
{T}: Jagged-Scar Archers deals damage equal to its power to target creature with flying.

card.name: Harvest Season
card.oracle_text: Search your library for up to X basic land cards, where X is the number of tapped creatures you control, put those cards onto the battlefield tapped, then shuffle.
card.flavor_text: A true reflection of nature: death fostering life.

card.name: Jungle Hollow
card.oracle_text:
Jungle Hollow enters tapped.
When Jungle Hollow enters, you gain 1 life.
{T}: Add {B} or {G}.

card.name: Llanowar Tribe
card.oracle_text: {T}: Add {G}{G}{G}.
card.flavor_text: "Llanowar remembers the Ice Age, the Phyrexian Invasion, and the Rift Era. So long as we draw breath, we will ensure such disasters never threaten our world again."

card.name: Lys Alana Scarblade
card.oracle_text: {T}, Discard an Elf card: Target creature gets -X/-X until end of turn, where X is the number of Elves you control.
card.flavor_text: In beauty-obsessed Lys Alana, one cut of her blade means the difference between a high society feast and raking through the dungheap for scraps.

card.name: Masked Admirers
card.oracle_text:
When Masked Admirers enters, draw a card.
Whenever you cast a creature spell, you may pay {G}{G}. If you do, return Masked Admirers from your graveyard to your hand.
card.flavor_text: "Beauty determines value, and we determine beauty."

card.name: Marwyn, the Nurturer
card.oracle_text:
Whenever another Elf you control enters, put a +1/+1 counter on Marwyn, the Nurturer.
{T}: Add an amount of {G} equal to Marwyn's power.
card.flavor_text: Midwife to mothers and leader to all.

card.name: Miara, Thorn of the Glade
card.oracle_text:
Whenever Miara, Thorn of the Glade or another Elf you control dies, you may pay {1} and 1 life. If you do, draw a card.
Partner (You can have two commanders if both have partner.)
card.flavor_text: "Approach from downwind. Tread with care. Aim for the heart."

card.name: Moldervine Reclamation
card.oracle_text: Whenever a creature you control dies, you gain 1 life and draw a card.
card.flavor_text:
"The heroes of the past nourish our spirits by their example—and nourish our crops by their decay."
—Jeddeg, philosopher of graves

card.name: Path of Ancestry
card.oracle_text:
Path of Ancestry enters tapped.
{T}: Add one mana of any color in your commander's color identity. When that mana is spent to cast a creature spell that shares a creature type with your commander, scry 1. (Look at the top card of your library. You may put that card on the bottom.)

card.name: Myriad Landscape
card.oracle_text:
Myriad Landscape enters tapped.
{T}: Add {C}.
{2}, {T}, Sacrifice Myriad Landscape: Search your library for up to two basic land cards that share a land type, put them onto the battlefield tapped, then shuffle.

card.name: Nullmage Shepherd
card.oracle_text: Tap four untapped creatures you control: Destroy target artifact or enchantment.
card.flavor_text: The Skelle spent days carving runes and erecting their scorn poles. The herd crushed them to splinters in seconds.

card.name: Numa, Joraga Chieftain
card.oracle_text:
At the beginning of combat on your turn, you may pay {X}{X}. When you do, distribute X +1/+1 counters among any number of target Elves.
Partner (You can have two commanders if both have partner.)
card.flavor_text: His blade carves a path for his people. His words guide them along it.

card.name: Poison-Tip Archer
card.oracle_text:
Reach (This creature can block creatures with flying.)
Deathtouch (Any amount of damage this deals to a creature is enough to destroy it.)
Whenever another creature dies, each opponent loses 1 life.
card.flavor_text: "One more step and you're mine."

card.name: Putrefy
card.oracle_text: Destroy target artifact or creature. It can't be regenerated.
card.flavor_text:
"All matter, animate or not, rots when exposed to time. We merely speed up the process."
—Ezoc, Golgari rot farmer

card.name: Reclamation Sage
card.oracle_text: When Reclamation Sage enters, you may destroy target artifact or enchantment.
card.flavor_text: "What was once formed by masons, shaped by smiths, or given life by mages, I will return to the embrace of the earth."

card.name: Pride of the Perfect
card.oracle_text: Elves you control get +2/+0.
card.flavor_text: Like moonglove's flowers, the greatest beauty often masks the greatest dangers.

card.name: Rhys the Exiled
card.oracle_text:
Whenever Rhys the Exiled attacks, you gain 1 life for each Elf you control.
{B}, Sacrifice an Elf: Regenerate Rhys the Exiled.
card.flavor_text: Once a famed hunter and packmaster, now a renegade seeking his own path.

card.name: Shaman of the Pack
card.oracle_text: When Shaman of the Pack enters, target opponent loses life equal to the number of Elves you control.
card.flavor_text: To the elves, her spear is a compass; to the boggarts, a harbinger of doom.

card.name: Sol Ring
card.oracle_text: {T}: Add {C}{C}.
card.flavor_text: Lost to time is the artificer's art of trapping light from a distant star in a ring of purest gold.

card.name: Springbloom Druid
card.oracle_text: When Springbloom Druid enters, you may sacrifice a land. If you do, search your library for up to two basic land cards, put them onto the battlefield tapped, then shuffle.
card.flavor_text: "New growth applies a healing poultice to wounds long scabbed over."

card.name: Sylvan Messenger
card.oracle_text:
Trample (This creature can deal excess combat damage to the player or planeswalker it's attacking.)
When Sylvan Messenger enters, reveal the top four cards of your library. Put all Elf cards revealed this way into your hand and the rest on the bottom of your library in any order.

card.name: Twinblade Assassins
card.oracle_text: At the beginning of your end step, if a creature died this turn, draw a card.
card.flavor_text: Rumors swirl of a pair of deadly Golgari assassins known only as the Left and Right Hands of the Ochran.

card.name: Timberwatch Elf
card.oracle_text: {T}: Target creature gets +X/+X until end of turn, where X is the number of Elves on the battlefield.
card.flavor_text: "If you ever want to leave this forest, now's the time."

card.name: Voice of Many
card.oracle_text: When Voice of Many enters, draw a card for each opponent who controls fewer creatures than you.
card.flavor_text: His words echo every roar, screech, and howl of the wilds.

card.name: Voice of the Woods
card.oracle_text: Tap five untapped Elves you control: Create a 7/7 green Elemental creature token with trample.
card.flavor_text: "Ancient ones, I call on you, your wisdom and your power, your will to claim again all that is rightfully yours."

card.name: Wirewood Channeler
card.oracle_text: {T}: Add X mana of any one color, where X is the number of Elves on the battlefield.
card.flavor_text: "Your words are meaningless. The rustling of leaves is the only language that makes any sense."

card.name: Wood Elves
card.oracle_text: When Wood Elves enters, search your library for a Forest card, put that card onto the battlefield, then shuffle.
card.flavor_text: Every branch a crossroads, every vine a swift steed.
